A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The program element funds the Air Force Operational Test and Evaluation Center (AFOTEC) to conduct Congressionally mandated Initial Operational Test and
Evaluation (IOT&E) to support major weapon system acquisition decisions beyond Low-Rate Initial Production (LRIP), Milestone C, full rate production, fielding, and
declaration of Initial Operational Capability (IOC). IOT&E is conducted to determine the operational effectiveness and suitability, and resolve overall mission capability, of
systems undergoing research and development (R&D) efforts.

 This PE funds participation in Multiservice Operational Test and Evaluation (MOT&E), and Follow-on Operational Test and Evaluation (FOT&E) when the continuation
 of IOT&E activities passed the full rate production decision. FOT&E answers specific questions about unresolved COIs and test issues or completes areas not finished
 during the IOT&E.

 The PE funds related Operational Test & Evaluation (OT&E) activities such as conducting Continuous Operational Testing (COT), Early Influence, agile release tests,
 Integrated Test and Evaluation (IT&E), Operational Utility Evaluations (OUE), Early Operational Assessments (EOA), Operational Assessments (OA) and operationally
 realistic evaluations of advanced technologies which informs military utility determination. These tests support releases and major milestones and decision points prior to
 Milestone C, full rate production, fielding, or declaration of IOC.

 IOT&E programs are identified in three system categories: Air; Weapons; and Command, Control, Communications, Computers, Intelligence, Surveillance and
 Reconnaissance (C4ISR).

 This program is in Budget Activity 6, RDT&E Management Support because this budget activity includes research, development, test and evaluation efforts and funds to
 sustain and/or modernize the installations or operations required for general research, development, test and evaluation.




