 Project CS2: Explosive Ordnance Disposal Render Safe - Sets Kits and Outfits (EOD RS-SKO) provides for the demonstration and evaluation of emerging technologies
 within requirements trade-space and capabilities needed for Explosive Ordnance Disposal (EOD) teams to Render Safe (RS) US and foreign ordnance and explosive
 hazards. Technical refresh of capabilities ensures Army EOD formations maintain overmatch capability. EOD RS-SKO equips EOD teams with a suite of 11 capabilities
 needed to safely and effectively render safe explosive threats. Lessons learned from Ukraine and Israeli conflict show that the enemy/threat changes constantly--
 UAS and ground robotics tactics, techniques and procedures (TTPs), countermeasures, long range fires, trench warfare, obstacles and electronic countermeasures
 continue to evolve, so EOD RSSKO capabilities must keep pace to ensure overmatch. Near term technical refresh priorities include improved load sets for the Electronic
 Countermeasures (Modi and AN/PLT-6(v)1) to ensure the most current threats are being countered allowing EOD Techs to safely approach/render safe explosive
 threats and enhanced buried explosive hazard detection to allow EOD Techs to quickly and effectively clear their pathway and/or identify threats for render safe
 missions. This project will continue to support cross-service initiatives to increase commonality among information reporting and control systems.

 Project DO6: Lethal & Protective Payloads for sUAS
 The Army has immediate need for lethal effects delivered by uncrewed systems to maintain overmatch against competitors that have unprecedented access to lethal,
 low-cost autonomous systems. The Lethal & Protective Payloads project will enable sUAS delivered effects through the Picatinny Common Lethality Integration Kit
 (CLIK) which consists of physical, electrical, and data interface design standards and an ecosystem of compliant hardware modules to enable rapid integration of an
 sUAS delivered munition suite. The Picatinny CLIK ecosystem consists of a Weapon Release System (WRS), Fire Control Module, Fuze Module, Radio Module, Power
 Module, and adapters for various common platforms and payload types. The munition suite will consist of legacy and commercial munitions to sUAS delivered lethality
 (e.g, dropped, launched, fired, or emplaced). The resulting lethal & protective capabilities delivered from sUAS will be anti-personnel, anti-materiel, obscuration, hazard
 neutralization, and deception. The use of Picatinny CLIK ensures that the Army does not procure and field one-off proprietary solutions that reduce sUAS platform and
 payload modularity and interoperability which would reduce operational effectiveness and increase sustainment costs.




