       Change Summary Explanation
       The FY 2026 President's Budget submittal did not reflect the FY 2027 through FY 2030 funding. Therefore, an explanation of the changes between the two
       budget positions for FY2027 cannot be made in a relevant manner.

       FY 2026 has been adjusted due to Congressional Directed Reduction of $18.398 million.

       FY 2026 (Current Year) to FY 2027 (Budget Year) funding increased by $168.006 million, due to: $155.234 million increase for Long Range Kill Chain test
       capability development; restoration of $18.398 million Congressional Directed Reduction; $4.079 million increase for test infrastructure corrections; $3.839 million
       increase for hypersonic ground test infrastructure; $2.515 million increase for inflation; $15.852 million decrease of test and evaluation Hypersonics multi-year
       add; and $0.207 million decrease for Stargazer Withhold, baseline adjustments, balancers, and internal corrections.

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                    FY 2025      FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: Facility restoration and modernization at the 96TW                                                                                 14.261       15.794        10.515
Description: Facility restoration and modernization at the 96TW

FY 2026 Plans:
For FY 2026 Current Year, the 96TW is performing Restoration and Modernization (R&M) efforts across the range complex,
including repair/replacement of Heating, Ventilation and Air Conditioning (HVAC), install/upgrade perimeter power, and expand
asphalt for the Tactical Datalinks Test Lab; design for secondary fluid system and repair lowslope roofs at McKinley Climatic
Laboratory; and roof repairs for the Central Control Facility (CCF).
FY 2027 Plans:
96 TW FY 2027 Budget Year plans include HVAC, plumbing, and electrical facility system repairs for multiple test facilities;
planning charettes for the range communications facility; fluid replacement and storm damage repair at McKinley Climatic
Laboratory; multiple roof replacements; and planning charrette/design/construction for several failing facilities.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Funding decreased $5.279 million due to completion of major HVAC repairs and return to normal funding levels.
Title: Facility restoration and modernization at AEDC                                                                                     70.615      176.668       345.482
Description: Facility restoration and modernization at AEDC

FY 2026 Plans:
For FY 2026 Current Year, AEDC is performing restoration and modernization projects across geographically separated locations
with increased emphasis on hypersonic test capabilities, including major repair and replacement projects supporting the Von

Management Support

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                   FY 2025    FY 2026      FY 2027
Karmon Facility, J6 large rocket motor test facility, Aerodynamic and Propulsion Test Unit (APTU), C-Plant, test utility systems,
and various test facilities across Arnold AFB and the 704TG.
FY 2027 Plans:
AEDC FY 2027 Budget Year plans include major restoration and modernization stopgap measures at the Central Inertial and GPS
Test Facility (CIGTF) the Holloman High Speed Test Track (HHSTT), and the National Radar Cross-Section Test Facility (NRTF)
as bridges to future MILCONs; major shared mechanical, electrical, and cooling water system infrastructure recapitalization efforts
at the Aeropropulsion Systems Test Facility (ASTF), the Von Karmon Gas Dynamics Facility (VKF) Plant, and the Propulsion
Wind Tunnel (PWT) Plant; targeted test facility modernization efforts at the 16ft diameter Supersonic Wind Tunnel (16S), the
Aeropropulsion Test Unit (APTU), and the Turbine Engine Altitude test cells. Begin infrastructure projects to support Long Range
Kill Web capability development.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Funding increased $168.814 million to develop Long Range Kill Chain test capabilities.
Title: Facility restoration and modernization at 412 TW                                                                                  9.952        6.901       11.372
Description: Facility restoration and modernization at the 412 TW

FY 2026 Plans:
For FY 2026 Current Year, the 412 TW is performing restoration and modernization projects for various T&E facilities. Major
projects include renovation of the aircraft engine repair shop, fire suppression to support the Ridley Mission Control Center and
fuel cell dock, design work to remove/replace an elevator in the Benefield Anechoic Facility, and control room upgrades for the
Joint Simulation Environment (JSE).
FY 2027 Plans:
412 TW FY 2027 Budget Year plans include multiple phased secure facility, power, and test cooling system upgrades for the
Benefield Anechoic Facility; multiple upgrades to the test engineering software lab to include HVAC replacement, safety/security
improvements, fire suppression system replacement and renovation of the warehouse storage and loading dock; and fire alarm
distribution upgrades for the telemetry van maintenance shop.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Funding increased $4.471 million due to funding transfers related to real property appropriation corrections.
