Title: Bomber Supplemental Trainer Aircrew Readiness (BSTAR )                                                                -       0.000      56.300           -      56.300
Description: The Bomber Supplemental Trainer for Aircrew Readiness (BSTAR) program is designed to
enhance the proficiency of bomber aircrew
by introducing Contractor-Owned, Contractor-Operated (COCO) supplemental training operations to enhance
aircrew proficiency through airmanship, instrument proficiency, and Crew Resource Management (CRM) for
bomber aircrew. It is intended to enhance and sustain foundational airmanship, instrument proficiency, and
crew coordination skills outside the primary Mission Design Series (MDS), using a high-tempo, low-cost
supplemental trainer. Performance data, training outcomes, and airmanship development trends from this effort
will inform decisions regarding sustainment, scaling, and potential enterprise implementation of a steady-state
BSTAR Companion Trainer Program. This initiative aligns with USAF strategic objectives to improve B-1 aircrew
operational efficiency across its bomber fleet. This program will aim to aid the B-1 aviators through supplemental
training throughout the aircrew members' careers within Air Force Global Strike Command.

