A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Guam on-island Cyber team coordinates local network defense activities and assumes responsibility to defend onsite assets from active or imminent cyberspace threats
in the event of degraded communication conditions. This Budget Project provides the oversight and inter-Agency/Service coordination for Cyber activities needed for
integrating a capability to defend Guam against ballistic, hypersonic, and cruise missile attack.

