D. Acquisition Strategy
Acquisition strategy for Guam Defense consists of contract actions to industry, and agreements with Department of Defense (DoD) organizations and Federally Funded
Research and Development Centers to develop, demonstrate, and field a Missile Defense System on Guam. MDA is leveraging existing programs of record with
existing and planned contracts. Major contributors include Aegis Weapon System; contributing capabilities as part of its future deliveries to support the AGS, and AN/
TPY-6 Radar development. The AN/TPY-6 is the joint designation for the Homeland Defense Radar-Guam and is a sensor for the AGS.




