Title: Acquisition Management in support of PEO Business Enterprise Systems                                                               3.574       3.637          9.842
Description: Funds DAF IT test network, enterprise solutions in support of DAF business solutions, and PEO early acquisition
planning and testing activities. Provides funding for network operations necessary to maintain Gunter DAF IT Test Base
responsible for testing of critical software patches prior to DAF-wide release. Supports early lifecycle planning and business
capability acquisition expertise, leveraging adaptive concepts for emerging solutions. Funds critical enterprise-wide requirements,
including research licenses, workforce training, and analytical support, to directly enable SECAF and SAF/AQ priorities.

FY 2026 Plans:
Funding will be allocated to PEO BES network operations delivering critical network management and pre-release testing of
software patches prior to deployment to DAF. Enables PEO to effectively manage its portfolio of enterprise applications through
funding of workforce training and acquisition support.
FY 2027 Plans:
Funding will be allocated to PEO BES network operations, early acquisition planning, and enterprise-wide initiatives to align DAF
business systems with strategic priorities.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increase is to support a backlog of requirements for PEO/BES. This was under funded in previous years.
Title: Technical and Analytical Support                                                                                                   0.000       2.220          0.000
Description: Supports Acquisition Domain-level effort to integrate existing acquisition business systems/services, data, and
processes supporting key Acquisition capabilities at the enterprise level (via the Acquisition Domain Capabilities Integration
(ADCI) activities). This support entails analysis required to architect an integrated environment on multiple hosting platforms to
support the portfolio of acquisition business systems by solving problems across/outside of individual system boundaries with
the goal of reducing redundancy, improving systems operations, and improving management of data resulting in dramatically
improved transparency, efficiency, and effective management of the Acquisition process. This support also helps implement
standards for data management and service-oriented design methodology to facilitate efficiency and interoperability as well
as providing some business intelligence services. The creation and support of domain-level requirements and governance
processes as well as the creation of domain-wide data standards are additional support items provided. In addition, includes
support for Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning (AI/ML) pilots, experimentation associated with business analytics, acquisition
program performance measures, and predictive analytics in support of decision-making and workforce training for the acquisition
enterprise.

FY 2026 Plans:

                                                                                    nt Support                                         Integration

