Increase of $27K from FY 2026 will allow the Department of the Air Force to identify, develop, and negotiate more IAs in FY 2027.
Title: Engineer and Scientist Exchange Program/Administrative and Professional Exchange Program (ESEP/APEP)                               0.500       0.500          0.500
Description: Oversight, program execution, program management, and selection of Engineer and Scientist Exchange Program
(ESEP) and Administrative and Professional Exchange Program (APEP) Agreements with partner governments. Military and
civilian personnel from Department of the Air Force (DAF) Command, Research Centers, Test Centers, and Logistic Centers for 2-
year tours at selected allied partner government laboratories and facilities. Partner government military and civilian personnel are
placed in DAF Research, Development, Test and Evaluation (RDT&E) facilities.

FY 2026 Plans:
