Title: ARSR-4 Replacement Hawaii (ARSR4R-HI)                                                                                         66.717      47.298        44.187
Description: The ARSR4R-HI will be the Ground-Based detection, discrimination, and tracking radar to support defense of
Hawaii. It will replace the current ARSR-4 radar located on Mount Ka'ala (4,019 ft in elevation), Oahu, Hawaii. The radar will
provide data to multiple DoD and FAA missions simultaneously, including Area Air Defense (AAD), Air Traffic Control (ATC),
and Traffic Management. The radar suite will provide increased sensitivity using mature state of the art technologies, increase
performance in multi-mission operations, provide modularity, flexibility, and growth opportunities.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Site design and preparation efforts ongoing
- Preliminary Design review with each vendor
- Collaborating with the Golden Dome for America Direct Reporting Program Manager's Office with respect to the defense of
Hawaii
FY 2027 Plans:
- Complete gap analysis considering Golden Dome of America (GDA) capability
- Reassess technical solution to meet Air Traffic Control surveillance and Air Domain Awareness
- Begin system procurement for Mt Ka'ala site
- Continue to collaborate with GDA by sharing Preliminary Design Review (PDR) and tech demo data from prior year development
effrorts
