Operational Systems Development$$, $$In order to meet the PACAF/INDOPACOM DoD/FAA urgent mission needs, a Middle Tier of Acquisition Rapid Development strategy was planned for the ARSR4R-
HI replacement system. The acquisition strategy included demonstration of two capable systems and down select to a single vendor. However, requirement changes
halted this strategy after Technology Demonstrations and Preliminary Design Reviews were conducted, just prior to down select solicitation. The program office will
provide this body of data for consideration by other Department of War efforts but will pivot acquisition strategies in FY26 to focus on the remaining requirement set,
leveraging the existing site preparation analysis.

 This effort is being maintained in the office of Air Force Program Executive Officer (Electronic Systems). Program support, cost, contracts, logistics, and financial
 management support is managed by Air Force Life Cycle Management Center Aerospace Management Systems Division (AFLCMC/ESA).

 The National Airspace System Defense Program /Long Range Radar Joint Program Office (NAS/LRR JPO) will provide long-term Operations and Sustainment in FY32
 and beyond.

