A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Prior to FY 2026, this budget line item funded the replacement of the current Air Route Surveillance Radar Version 4 (ARSR-4) on Mt. Ka'ala, Hawaii (ARSR4R-HI) to
include prototype development, test, site preparation, and installation. The responsibility for missile defense has been consolidated under the Golden Dome for America
(GDA) architecture, which supersedes the former Air Force-specific requirement in Hawaii.

 This budget line item now funds the remaining requirement for replacement of the legacy ARSR4 radar on Mt. Ka'ala with a dual-use material solution meeting both the
 Air Force, Air Domain Awareness and the FAA, Air Traffic Control (ATC) missions.

 This program element may include necessary civilian pay expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such programs
 funds would be in addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program element 0605827F, 0605828F, 0605829F, 0605831F, 0605832F, 0605833F, 0605898F,
 0606398F.

 This program is in Budget Activity 7, Operational System Development because this budget activity includes development efforts to upgrade systems that have been
 fielded or have received approval for full rate production and anticipate production funding in the current or subsequent fiscal year.

