 T-38 Operational System Development effort provides advanced trainers for Specialized Undergraduate Pilot Training and Introduction to Fighter Fundamentals, and is
 a test bed for fighter-type aircraft capability. The T-38A/B/C is a is a twin-engine, two-seat (tandem), supersonic jet trainer used by AETC, Air Combat Command and Air
 Force Global Strike Command as a companion trainer in Adversary Air (ADAIR) exercises supporting U-2 operational units, F-22 readiness, and B-2 operational units.
 There are currently 486 operational T-38s in the Air Force inventory (53 T-38A, six T-38B and 427 T-38C).

