Title: Small Business Innovation Research & Small Business Technology Transfer                                                      904.678       0.000        0.000
Description: The Small Business Innovation Research (SBIR) and Small Business Technology Transfer (STTR) program
implements 15 U.S.C Section 638 to maximize the creative, innovative, and entrepreneurial spirit of small businesses to solve
technological problems. AFWERX's mission is to accelerate agile and affordable capability transitions by teaming leaders in
innovative technology with Airmen and Guardian talent.

The DAF SBIR/STTR program implements three different approaches to provide funding and opportunities to small businesses:

Open Topic: The Open Topic Program uses a technology-agnostic solicitation which encourages commercial industry to
submit dual-use technology solutions without having a known end-user. It is used to capture the best capabilities and emerging
technologies and allows industry to bring novel solutions to the DAF.

USAF awarded 235 million dollars under the Open topic approach with FY25 funds, with additional awards expected.

Since its inception in FY19, the Open Topic program has awarded over 6,400 contracts worth 3.993 billion dollars to small
businesses, demonstrating its significant impact on the defense innovation base. The program remains a vital pathway for
accessing a diverse range of dual-use technologies and fostering a robust defense innovation base.

Specific Topic: The Specific Topic Program seeks innovative solutions for SECAF identified operational development priorities
and defined problem sets by a DAF end user or customer. Specific Topics have clearly-defined requirements and a known DAF
customer built into the topic solicitation.

Management Support

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                  FY 2025    FY 2026      FY 2027

USAF awarded 233 million dollars under the specific topic approach utilizing FY25 funds, with additional awards expected.

STRATFI/TACFI: The STRATFI (Strategic Funding Increase) and TACFI (Tactical Funding Increase) Programs help to scale
Phase II efforts to the level needed to achieve technology transitions. These program de-risk development through syndication
with multiple transition-focused partners and leveraging outside investment.

Funding amounts within the STRATFI program range from 3 million to 15 million per defense project, excluding other government
and venture funding that can potentially quadruple the total award amount. Under the TACFI program, contracts range between
375,000 dollars and 2 million dollars.

Utilizing FY25 funds, AFWERX awarded 68 TACFI and 18 STRATFI contracts across various topics valued at 213 million
dollars. STRATFI topics included: rapidly deployable precision landing, Artificial Intelligence (AI) assisted tools, hard target
surveillance radar, on-site manufacturing of jet fuel, augmented reality for maintenance training, hypersonic missile development,
decisions on edge, sensor fusion and automation, expeditionary manufacturing, strike enhancement technologies, advanced
engine component development, weather forecasting, data mining, advanced manufacturing, and alternate sensor deployment
mechanisms. TACFI topics include technical areas of Artificial Intelligence, hypersonic technologies, human performance,
materials & manufacturing, cross domain technologies, munition technologies, information dominance, aerospace systems,
directed energy, digital capabilities, and advanced sensor technologies.

FY 2026 Plans:
If reauthorized, FY 2026 SBIR/STTR funds will continue to align with USAF priorities and needs while continuing investments
in the emerging technologies that may result in future capabilities. Investment allocations will be made in Open Topic, Specific
Topic, and TACFI/STRATFI programs and associated administrative costs based on demand signals, timeliness of funds
allocation and availability, and changes to strategic guidance or priorities.
FY 2027 Plans:
If reauthorized, FY 2027 SBIR/STTR funds will continue to align with USAF priorities and needs while continuing investments
in the emerging technologies that may result in future capabilities. Investment allocations will be made in Open Topic, Specific
Topic, and TACFI/STRATFI programs and associated administrative costs based on demand signals, timeliness of funds
allocation and availability, and changes to strategic guidance or priorities.
